1
00:01:24,359 --> 00:01:26,879
You little brats, finally here.

2
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:28,359
General Chen, forgive our delay.

3
00:01:28,680 --> 00:01:29,560
Please pardon us, General.

4
00:01:29,760 --> 00:01:31,159
I'll deal with you later.

5
00:01:31,680 --> 00:01:32,599
Hurry, take this boy

6
00:01:32,719 --> 00:01:34,239
back to the manor for proper treatment.

7
00:01:35,079 --> 00:01:35,560
Thank you.

8
00:01:35,680 --> 00:01:36,079
Yes, sir.

9
00:01:47,719 --> 00:01:50,239
Ning Ziming, as Minister of Rites,

10
00:01:50,640 --> 00:01:51,599
a man of Confucian learning,

11
00:01:52,239 --> 00:01:55,200
always preaching virtue and propriety.

12
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:56,519
Who would have thought

13
00:01:56,879 --> 00:01:59,400
he'd raise three rotten brats like you.

14
00:02:01,879 --> 00:02:02,319
You old...

15
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,200
General Chen,

16
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:06,040
today's incident is all a misunderstanding.

17
00:02:06,319 --> 00:02:07,280
You are a man of great virtue and renown,

18
00:02:07,439 --> 00:02:08,960
who rarely appears in the capital.

19
00:02:09,599 --> 00:02:11,520
I hope you'll be magnanimous

20
00:02:11,919 --> 00:02:13,840
and not hold it against my two brothers.

21
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:15,599
What?

22
00:02:16,319 --> 00:02:18,759
Not calling me "old codger" anymore?

23
00:02:19,719 --> 00:02:20,560
General Chen,

24
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:23,080
my brothers offended you first.

25
00:02:23,319 --> 00:02:24,960
As the eldest son of Ning Manor,

26
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:27,479
I offer my apologies here and now.

27
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:30,000
I beg your forgiveness.

28
00:02:32,560 --> 00:02:33,080
Big Brother, Second Brother,

29
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:34,039
what are you afraid of?

30
00:02:34,400 --> 00:02:35,719
Who told him to hide his identity?

31
00:02:36,120 --> 00:02:36,759
Besides,

32
00:02:36,919 --> 00:02:38,240
our grandfather is the Left Chancellor,

33
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:39,479
also serving as Minister of Revenue.

34
00:02:39,879 --> 00:02:40,759
The troops' provisions and pay

35
00:02:41,039 --> 00:02:42,280
all depend on him, don't they?

36
00:02:42,599 --> 00:02:43,199
Why should we fear him?

37
00:02:44,039 --> 00:02:44,719
Third Brother,

38
00:02:45,439 --> 00:02:46,080
am I wrong?

39
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:49,199
Our army has lost battle after battle lately.

40
00:02:49,599 --> 00:02:50,560
These crude generals,

41
00:02:50,719 --> 00:02:51,560
if they truly had any skill,

42
00:02:51,719 --> 00:02:52,759
should go reclaim the lost lands!

43
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:53,319
Useless fools.

44
00:02:53,319 --> 00:02:54,439
Strutting around in front of us youngsters,

45
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,479
what's the point of all that posturing?

46
00:02:55,599 --> 00:02:56,080
How dare you!

47
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,879
Shut up, you fool!

48
00:02:58,000 --> 00:02:58,439
I...

49
00:02:58,919 --> 00:02:59,960
Are you saying

50
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,560
that our defeats in battle

51
00:03:02,240 --> 00:03:03,599
are the soldiers' fault?

52
00:03:05,280 --> 00:03:06,080
That's right!

53
00:03:08,800 --> 00:03:09,319
Fine.

54
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,039
You ignorant brat,

55
00:03:13,319 --> 00:03:14,400
who's never set foot on a battlefield,

56
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:16,560
yet you dare to spout such nonsense here!

57
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:19,159
Without our troops,

58
00:03:19,319 --> 00:03:20,439
braving the snow and ice,

59
00:03:20,759 --> 00:03:21,800
risking their lives in battle,

60
00:03:22,319 --> 00:03:23,960
where would your wealth and glory come from?

61
00:03:25,039 --> 00:03:25,520
Guards!

62
00:03:26,039 --> 00:03:26,479
Sir!

63
00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:27,439
Seize him!

64
00:03:27,599 --> 00:03:28,919
Bring him to the palace at once.

65
00:03:29,080 --> 00:03:29,560
Wait, Big Brother...

66
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:32,039
I'll ask Ning Ziming and the Left Chancellor face to face

67
00:03:32,719 --> 00:03:33,840
who is truly to blame

68
00:03:34,479 --> 00:03:35,879
for these military defeats!

69
00:03:36,400 --> 00:03:37,039
General, please calm your anger.

70
00:03:37,159 --> 00:03:37,639
Stop!

71
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:39,520
Father!

72
00:03:39,879 --> 00:03:40,360
Father!

73
00:03:40,639 --> 00:03:41,800
Please, save us!

74
00:03:44,479 --> 00:03:45,199
General,

75
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:47,080
what has happened here?

76
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:49,960
You'd better

77
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:52,280
ask those fine sons of yours.

78
00:03:55,719 --> 00:03:56,319
Speak up.

79
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:57,479
What happened?

80
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:58,520
Where's your fourth brother?

81
00:03:59,319 --> 00:03:59,759
Father,

82
00:04:00,639 --> 00:04:02,319
today's incident was purely an accident.

83
00:04:02,840 --> 00:04:04,560
I thought our fourth brother was frail and weak,

84
00:04:04,919 --> 00:04:07,000
worried he was going hungry and cold outside,

85
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:09,439
so I came to bring him back to the manor today.

86
00:04:10,759 --> 00:04:13,960
But he held a grudge about leaving the manor,

87
00:04:14,400 --> 00:04:16,319
and during the scuffle, he fell and got hurt.

88
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:17,560
I truly...

89
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:18,360
He's hurt?

90
00:04:19,240 --> 00:04:19,759
Where is he?

91
00:04:20,279 --> 00:04:20,680
I don't know.

92
00:04:20,800 --> 00:04:21,360
You don't know?!

93
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:24,120
The General has sent Ning Chen back to the manor for treatment.

94
00:04:25,879 --> 00:04:27,680
You two, hurry to the General's Mansion

95
00:04:27,959 --> 00:04:29,160
and bring the Fourth Young Master back to recover.

96
00:04:29,720 --> 00:04:30,160
Yes, Father.

97
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:33,160
Father,

98
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:34,720
we truly didn't know

99
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:36,600
General Chen Wu's true identity.

100
00:04:36,839 --> 00:04:37,360
That's why

101
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:39,879
I offended him with my words.

102
00:04:41,160 --> 00:04:41,639
Father,

103
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:42,959
today's incident

104
00:04:43,439 --> 00:04:44,879
has nothing to do with me at all.

105
00:04:46,240 --> 00:04:47,000
They can vouch for me.

106
00:04:47,160 --> 00:04:48,040
What? Big Brother, you...

107
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:48,879
Shut your mouth!

108
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:50,279
Haven't you embarrassed us enough?

109
00:04:54,319 --> 00:04:54,800
No, I...

110
00:04:57,600 --> 00:04:58,199
General,

111
00:04:58,959 --> 00:05:00,399
These worthless sons of mine

112
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:01,759
are young and ignorant.

113
00:05:02,160 --> 00:05:03,399
Please forgive them.

114
00:05:03,519 --> 00:05:04,240
Lord Ning.

115
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:07,040
Do you know what your fine sons

116
00:05:07,199 --> 00:05:08,160
just said?

117
00:05:08,439 --> 00:05:09,040
What's more,

118
00:05:09,279 --> 00:05:10,800
they wanted to kill me.

119
00:05:10,920 --> 00:05:11,439
What?

120
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:13,240
No, you...

121
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:14,720
Who said that?

122
00:05:17,079 --> 00:05:17,920
Big Brother, Second Brother, you...

123
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:20,720
You wretched beast!

124
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:23,959
Father!

125
00:05:26,639 --> 00:05:28,240
How dare you!

126
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:29,240
Do you have any idea

127
00:05:29,639 --> 00:05:32,079
of the great service the General has rendered to our dynasty?

128
00:05:32,800 --> 00:05:33,839
When he was killing enemies on the battlefield,

129
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,120
you weren't even born yet!

130
00:05:35,639 --> 00:05:37,600
Enemy states offered a million taels of gold for his life

131
00:05:37,800 --> 00:05:38,360
and still couldn't take it.

132
00:05:38,519 --> 00:05:40,439
Who gave you the gall to speak like that?

133
00:05:41,079 --> 00:05:41,800
Father, stop hitting me!

134
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:42,680
I was wrong!

135
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:46,040
Father!

136
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:49,199
Third Brother, don't blame me.

137
00:05:49,439 --> 00:05:51,600
Noble house rivalries have always been this way.

138
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:55,839
General,

139
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:58,160
I have failed to raise my sons properly.

140
00:05:58,639 --> 00:05:59,759
But please rest assured.

141
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,240
I'll take them home today

142
00:06:01,399 --> 00:06:02,759
and discipline them severely.

143
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:05,240
Get out of here, now!

144
00:06:05,959 --> 00:06:06,600
Halt!

145
00:06:07,839 --> 00:06:09,199
You think you can leave just like that?

146
00:06:11,759 --> 00:06:13,279
He's pushing his luck.

147
00:06:13,759 --> 00:06:14,879
This old man,

148
00:06:15,279 --> 00:06:17,079
does he really take me for a pushover?

149
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:20,519
Have they caused some other trouble?

150
00:06:20,839 --> 00:06:21,480
Lord Ning,

151
00:06:22,240 --> 00:06:24,000
your fine sons

152
00:06:24,199 --> 00:06:26,600
said our recent military defeats

153
00:06:26,759 --> 00:06:28,959
were all the troops' fault.

154
00:06:29,360 --> 00:06:30,079
They also said

155
00:06:30,439 --> 00:06:33,120
their grandfather, the Minister of Revenue,

156
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:36,519
is the one we brutes must all depend on.

157
00:06:36,879 --> 00:06:37,319
Come.

158
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:39,920
Let's go to the palace now and ask His Majesty

159
00:06:40,279 --> 00:06:41,839
just whose fault it really is.

160
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:45,439
Since when did the troops become the Left Chancellor's wards?

161
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:48,879
Has the Left Chancellor taken the court's funds and grain

162
00:06:49,079 --> 00:06:50,399
as his own?

163
00:06:50,639 --> 00:06:53,639
Does he not fear chilling the hearts of all our troops?

164
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:57,560
How could they cause such a huge disaster?

165
00:06:57,879 --> 00:06:58,360
This won't do.

166
00:06:58,920 --> 00:07:00,680
This must not be brought before His Majesty.

167
00:07:01,279 --> 00:07:01,839
Otherwise,

168
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:04,560
all of Ning Manor will be doomed.

169
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:07,240
General, please calm your anger.

170
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:11,839
We've served together at court for years.

171
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:14,720
How today's matter came to this,

172
00:07:15,399 --> 00:07:16,639
you and I both know well.

173
00:07:17,079 --> 00:07:18,120
Let's speak openly.

174
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:19,879
What do you want?

175
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:23,839
Lord Ning, what do you mean by that?

176
00:07:24,199 --> 00:07:26,399
You make it sound like I am extorting you.

177
00:07:26,920 --> 00:07:29,720
It is just that winter is almost upon us,

178
00:07:29,920 --> 00:07:32,040
yet the funds, grain, and padded coats

179
00:07:32,319 --> 00:07:33,480
have yet to be secured.

180
00:07:33,639 --> 00:07:35,600
Whenever I think of our troops

181
00:07:35,759 --> 00:07:37,480
having to endure hunger and cold again,

182
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,680
my heart truly cannot bear it.

183
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:42,319
The court just cut military pay.

184
00:07:42,759 --> 00:07:44,839
It seems this old man planned this all along.

185
00:07:45,399 --> 00:07:47,639
I did not expect him to have such cunning.

186
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:53,399
Our soldiers risk their lives for the realm.

187
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:55,199
How can we let them go hungry and cold?

188
00:07:55,759 --> 00:07:58,319
I will go back and petition His Majesty with the Left Chancellor at once

189
00:07:58,639 --> 00:07:59,639
to make sure

190
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,920
the soldiers' food and clothing are taken care of.

191
00:08:02,759 --> 00:08:03,399
On this matter,

192
00:08:04,079 --> 00:08:05,720
do you have the authority to decide?

193
00:08:06,759 --> 00:08:08,079
Rest assured, General.

194
00:08:08,600 --> 00:08:11,000
I believe all the officials at court

195
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:13,600
deeply care about our soldiers.

196
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,040
Take your fine sons,

197
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:21,439
and get out of here.

198
00:08:24,360 --> 00:08:25,120
Scram!

199
00:08:25,959 --> 00:08:26,680
Let's go, let's go.

200
00:08:31,079 --> 00:08:33,320
Thank you, General, for your magnanimity.

201
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:34,320
I shall take my leave.

202
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:35,000
Wait.

203
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:37,559
What is it now?

204
00:08:37,879 --> 00:08:38,559
Lord Ning.

205
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:40,200
Your reputation...

206
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:42,120
I shall say no more.

207
00:08:42,399 --> 00:08:43,720
I just want to tell you this:

208
00:08:43,879 --> 00:08:45,519
Ning Chen is a fine young man.

209
00:08:45,759 --> 00:08:47,960
If Ning Manor cannot accommodate him,

210
00:08:48,480 --> 00:08:51,159
let me take him to the army.

211
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:53,639
This is all a misunderstanding.

212
00:08:56,159 --> 00:08:57,840
Thank you, General, for the reminder.

213
00:08:58,559 --> 00:08:59,720
I know how to handle my own affairs.

214
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:01,120
Farewell. Farewell.

215
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:04,320
General.

216
00:09:04,600 --> 00:09:05,600
Are we just letting them go?

217
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:06,840
What more do you want?

218
00:09:07,759 --> 00:09:09,039
The troops now have

219
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:11,440
their winter provisions and padded coats.

220
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:13,840
You really want to take this to His Majesty?

221
00:09:14,039 --> 00:09:15,200
Let's quit while we're ahead.

222
00:09:15,919 --> 00:09:16,440
By the way,

223
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:18,559
we have disturbed this household.

224
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,440
When the master returns,

225
00:09:20,879 --> 00:09:22,080
give them some silver.

226
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:23,440
I have urgent business

227
00:09:23,960 --> 00:09:25,639
and must enter the palace at once.

228
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:26,840
Yes, sir.

229
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:34,840
How is he, Doctor?

230
00:09:37,879 --> 00:09:38,480
Lord Ning.

231
00:09:38,720 --> 00:09:40,840
The Fourth Young Master's condition is grave.

232
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:42,879
Malnourished, weak, and frail.

233
00:09:43,039 --> 00:09:44,399
His head was struck by a club.

234
00:09:44,639 --> 00:09:45,679
In the future, he might even...

235
00:09:46,799 --> 00:09:47,759
Spare me the details.

236
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:49,399
Treat him with the best medicine.

237
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,080
Rest assured, Lord Ning.

238
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,320
I will do my utmost.

239
00:09:53,639 --> 00:09:54,159
Steward,

240
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:56,399
go with the doctor yourself to fetch the medicine.

241
00:09:56,759 --> 00:09:58,000
And tell the kitchen

242
00:09:58,200 --> 00:09:59,240
to stew an old hen for him.

243
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:00,559
Yes, Master.

244
00:10:01,559 --> 00:10:02,000
One more thing.

245
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:04,720
Please keep today's matter confidential.

246
00:10:04,879 --> 00:10:05,799
Rest assured, Lord Ning.

247
00:10:05,960 --> 00:10:06,840
I understand.

248
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:08,519
I shall take my leave.

249
00:10:38,399 --> 00:10:38,879
Chen'er.

250
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:40,279
You're awake.

251
00:10:42,039 --> 00:10:42,799
Wasn't I at Xiaomei's place,

252
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:44,200
being harassed by Ning Xing and the others?

253
00:10:44,679 --> 00:10:45,360
How did I end up here?

254
00:10:53,919 --> 00:10:54,480
Chen'er.

255
00:10:55,039 --> 00:10:56,720
Is there something you want to tell your father?

256
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:05,440
You...

257
00:11:07,039 --> 00:11:07,600
No.

258
00:11:08,159 --> 00:11:10,200
This boy has caught His Majesty's eye now.

259
00:11:10,679 --> 00:11:11,399
I mustn't strike him.

260
00:11:13,279 --> 00:11:13,759
Chen'er.

261
00:11:14,240 --> 00:11:16,000
Why are you yanking your father's beard?

262
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:19,879
I wanted to make sure I wasn't dreaming.

263
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:23,159
Judging by your reaction,

264
00:11:23,919 --> 00:11:24,480
this isn't a dream.

265
00:11:25,159 --> 00:11:26,159
Of course it's not a dream.

266
00:11:26,799 --> 00:11:28,360
I do care about you.

267
00:11:29,159 --> 00:11:30,240
I've looked into this matter.

268
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:31,799
Your brothers

269
00:11:32,519 --> 00:11:33,600
didn't mean to hurt you.

270
00:11:33,919 --> 00:11:34,720
But don't worry,

271
00:11:34,879 --> 00:11:36,039
I have already disciplined them.

272
00:11:37,200 --> 00:11:38,919
Wow, this change in attitude.

273
00:11:39,559 --> 00:11:41,759
Did Chang Ruyue mess up his head or something?

274
00:11:43,879 --> 00:11:45,279
Lord Ning,

275
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:47,759
do you even hear yourself?

276
00:11:49,200 --> 00:11:50,240
I'm your father!

277
00:11:50,799 --> 00:11:52,679
Won't you even call me Father?

278
00:11:52,759 --> 00:11:53,240
Don't.

279
00:11:53,799 --> 00:11:54,639
Minister Ning,

280
00:11:55,240 --> 00:11:56,279
a father like you,

281
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:57,639
is too high an honor for me.

282
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,159
It might cost me my life.

283
00:12:00,559 --> 00:12:01,639
Just say it straight.

284
00:12:02,559 --> 00:12:03,600
What is it you actually want?

285
00:12:08,159 --> 00:12:08,679
Well...

286
00:12:08,840 --> 00:12:09,960
Brothers fighting at home,

287
00:12:10,159 --> 00:12:11,279
is a common occurrence.

288
00:12:11,759 --> 00:12:12,519
I feel that,

289
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:14,399
family scandals shouldn't be aired in public.

290
00:12:15,279 --> 00:12:17,039
Let's just drop this matter, shall we?

291
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:17,960
All right, Chen'er?

292
00:12:19,480 --> 00:12:20,200
Lord Ning,

293
00:12:20,639 --> 00:12:21,840
why don't you just call me Ning Chen?

294
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,000
It's easier on the ears.

295
00:12:23,559 --> 00:12:24,120
I know

296
00:12:24,399 --> 00:12:25,840
you don't like me.

297
00:12:26,399 --> 00:12:27,159
But what a coincidence,

298
00:12:27,320 --> 00:12:29,200
I don't like you either.

299
00:12:29,399 --> 00:12:30,080
Insolent boy!

300
00:12:30,639 --> 00:12:31,600
I am your father.

301
00:12:31,759 --> 00:12:32,600
Speaking to me like this,

302
00:12:32,759 --> 00:12:33,600
is completely unfilial!

303
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:35,000
There are no outsiders here.

304
00:12:35,159 --> 00:12:37,000
There's no need for the phony act with me.

305
00:12:37,240 --> 00:12:38,679
The reason you brought me back to Ning Manor,

306
00:12:38,799 --> 00:12:40,080
we both know full well.

307
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:42,039
If you truly have any conscience,

308
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,440
let me leave Ning Manor.

309
00:12:49,879 --> 00:12:51,600
You can't do any heavy labor.

310
00:12:51,759 --> 00:12:52,679
You're no scholar, and no warrior.

311
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:53,720
If you leave Ning Manor,

312
00:12:53,879 --> 00:12:55,279
you'll just starve to death on the streets.

313
00:12:55,399 --> 00:12:57,279
That's no concern of yours, Lord Ning.

314
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,080
Even if I starve to death,

315
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:00,759
I won't sully

316
00:13:00,919 --> 00:13:02,679
this auspicious ground of Ning Manor.

317
00:13:03,279 --> 00:13:04,000
So,

318
00:13:04,559 --> 00:13:06,720
please, Lord Ning, have mercy

319
00:13:07,759 --> 00:13:09,120
and let me go.

320
00:13:15,759 --> 00:13:16,200
Master.

321
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:22,919
You just woke up.

322
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:24,600
Your mind isn't clear yet.

323
00:13:25,799 --> 00:13:26,759
Here's a bowl of medicine.

324
00:13:27,080 --> 00:13:28,519
Drinking it will do you good.

325
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:32,679
I had this chicken soup specially prepared for you,

326
00:13:33,559 --> 00:13:34,559
to help restore your strength.

327
00:13:35,559 --> 00:13:37,440
Fourth Young Master, please drink the medicine.

328
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,159
There's poison in it, isn't there?

329
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:53,519
Fourth Young Master, you do love to jest.

330
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:55,759
The master truly does care

331
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,080
about you, Fourth Young Master.

332
00:13:57,480 --> 00:13:58,879
While you were unconscious,

333
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,399
the master stayed by your bedside,

334
00:14:00,559 --> 00:14:01,440
never leaving for a moment.

335
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:11,720
I have many official duties.

336
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:14,080
Get some rest early.

337
00:14:14,879 --> 00:14:16,480
I will come see you tomorrow morning.

338
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:17,720
Oh, by the way,

339
00:14:18,559 --> 00:14:20,159
Steward Liu will be guarding the door.

340
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:21,639
If you need anything,

341
00:14:22,639 --> 00:14:23,879
just call him.

342
00:14:32,919 --> 00:14:34,600
Such a swift change in attitude.

343
00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:38,039
What on earth is he so wary of?

